parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowouts can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden tire failure
tread separation
tire blowout
loss of tire pressure
damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Water Holding Tank Cover Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden detachment of the rear water holding tank cover while driving can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries. Additionally, the dragging cover can cause damage to the vehicle's undercarriage and surrounding components.
symptoms: The rear water holding tank cover comes off while driving
the cover is being held by plastic tubes
the cover is dragging on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stove burner's design can cause accidental ignition, leading to gas leaks, fires, or explosions, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The stove burners turn on unexpectedly
the stove burners leak gas
the stove burners can be easily accidentally turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Improperly Installed Lag Bolts in Awning Rail
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper installation of lag bolts in the awning rail can cause the awning to become loose and detach while driving, creating a road hazard and potentially causing accidents or damage to other vehicles.
symptoms: Awning vibrates or shakes excessively
awning comes loose or detaches while driving
lag bolts are loose or missing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped or split brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake excessively when applying the brakes, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates when applying the brakes
the brake pedal pulsates or feels spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to increased stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake warning light is illuminated.
